    <exprreq message="Dwarf required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Dwarf] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fBloodWar" name="Blood of the Warlord" description="You can influence a large number of orcs.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Orc, base Leadership score of 10+.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You are seen as a king among kings and a natural leader of orcs.  You gain a +2 bonus on all Diplomacy and Intimidate checks made to influence orcs.  Additionally, as long as you are visibly leading them, all your followers gain a +1 morale bonus on their attack rolls and Will saving throws.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="+2 Diplomacy and Intimidate when dealing with Orcs. +1 atk and Will allys.">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Orc required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Orc] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fBreatLink" name="Breathing Link" description="You can allow a person adjacent to you to breathe water.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Base Will save +2, aquatic elf or water genasi.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} As a free action on your turn, you may select one creature within 5 feet of you and give that creature the ability to breathe water as easily as you do. This supernatural ability renews automatically for that creature until you direct the ability to another creature or withdraw your power from it (a free action).\n\nThe creature&#146;s ability to breathe water ends immediately if you are separated by more than 5 feet or if you die, at which point the creature begins to drown if it is still underwater. This ability does not hamper the creature&#146;s ability to breathe air, nor does it change the creature&#146;s ability (or inability) to swim.\n\n{b}Special:{/b} You may select this feat more than once. Each time you take this feat, you may affect an additional creature with this ability. All such creatures need to remain within 5 feet of you (not each other). If one creature exceeds the range of this ability, it has no effect on the other creatures you are helping.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <comment>Aquatic Elf is not defined as its own race.</comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <exprreq message="Base Will +2 required."><![CDATA[child[vWill].field[vBase].value >= 2]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Water Genasi or Aquatic Elf required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.WatGenasi] + tagis[Race.Elf] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fCaliElem" name="Calishite Elementalist" description="You are a student of the Calishite tradition of elemental magic and have mastered its mysterious lore. You may choose to specialize in air magic or fire magic.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You gain +1 caster level when casting a spell from the Air tradition or Fire tradition, depending on which tradition you select when you choose this feat. This bonus caster level allows you to exceed the normal maximum damage allowed by a spell, so an 11th-level caster of the Air tradition creates an 11d6 lightning bolt instead of a 10d6 lightning bolt. If you are a wizard, you may add a spell in your tradition to your spellbook for free when you become able to cast it. This does not count against the two free spells you add to your spellbook at each class level.\n\nThe Tradition of Air magic consists of the following spells at\n\n{b}Tradition of Air                               Tradition of Fire{/b}\n0&#151;mage hand                              0&#151;flare\n1st&#151;shocking grasp                   1st&#151;burning hands\n2nd&#151;levitate                                 2nd&#151;pyrotechnics;\n3rd&#151;lightning bolt                       3rd&#151;fireball\n4th&#151;shout                                     4th&#151;wall of fire\n5th&#151;telekinesis                           5th&#151;dismissal\n6th&#151;chain lightning                    6th&#151;control weather\n7th&#151;reverse gravity                    7th&#151;delayed blast fireball\n8th&#151;Bigby&#146;s clenched fist         8th&#151;incendiary cloud\n9th&#151;Bigby&#146;s crushing hand      9th&#151;meteor swarm.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <comment>requires script to add spells for free</comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fCeleBlood" name="Celestial Bloodline" description="Some of your latent celestial abilities have matured.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Aasimar, base Fortitude, Reflex, and Will saves +1.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You gain the ability to use protection from evil three times per day and bless once per day as spell-like abilities with a caster level equal to your character level.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="Gains protection from evil and bless as a spell-like ability.">
    <comment>Aasimar Race tag not yet made.</comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Base Reflex +1 required."><![CDATA[child[vRef].field[vBase].value >= 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base Will +1 required."><![CDATA[child[vWill].field[vBase].value >= 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base Fortitude +1 required."><![CDATA[child[vFort].field[vBase].value >= 1]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fChonMiss" name="Chondathan Missionary" description="Your training has emphasized spells that help you spread the word of your faith.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Chondathan human, ability to cast divine spells.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You gain +1 caster level when casting a spell from the list below, or +2 caster level if you&#146;re actually using the spell to proselytize to a reasonably receptive audience (indifferent attitude or better).\n\nThe tradition of the Chondathan missionary consists of the following spells at the appropriate levels: \n0&#151;purify food and drink\n1st&#151;bless, sanctuary\n2nd&#151;calm emotions, consecrate, enthrall\n3rd&#151;prayer, remove disease\n4th&#151;discern lies, tongues\n5th&#151;atonement, hallow\n6th&#151;heroes&#146; feast\n7th&#151;resurrection\n8th&#151;mass heal\n9th&#151;miracle\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Human required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Human] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Ability to cast divine spells."><![CDATA[tagcount[Hero.Divine] >= 1]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fDeepDark" name="Deepening Darkness" description="Your inherent ability to create darkness is more powerful than normal.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Able to create darkness as a racial ability.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} The darkness you create with your racial ability is treated as {i}deeper darkness{/i} for the purpose of countering or being countered by spells such as {i}daylight{/i}. All other effects (duration, area of darkness, and so on) are as the {i}darkness{/i} spell.  You can use your darkness ability two additional times per day, so if you normally could use darkness as a spell-like ability 1/day, you can now use it 3/day.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fDuergMind" name="Duergar Mindshaper" description="You are accomplished at using the power of your mind to overcome weaker personalities.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Gray dwarf.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You gain +1 spell power (+1 on save DCs and a +1 bonus on checks to overcome spell resistance) on enchantment spells and spell-like abilities.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="+1 DC&apos;s and CL checks for your ench spells and spell-like abilties.">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <exprreq message="Duergar (Dwarf) required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Dwarf] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fEldrLing" name="Eldritch Lingquist" description="You have a deep understanding of how words themselves have their own kind of magic, and a mastery of the secret syntax of power.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Illuskan human, ability to cast divine spells.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You gain +1 caster level when casting a spell from the list below.\n\nThe tradition of the eldritch linguist consists of the following spells at the appropriate levels:\n0&#151;read magic\n1st&#151;command, comprehend languages\n2nd&#151;speak with animals, whispering wind\n3rd&#151;bestow curse, explosive runes, glyph of warding, speak with dead, speak with plants\n4th&#151;dismissal, sending, shout, tongues\n5th&#151;atonement, greater command, hallow\n6th&#151;greater glyph of warding, word of recall\n7th&#151;blasphemy, dictum, holy word, power word stun, word of chaos\n8th&#151;power word blind, symbol\n9th&#151;power word kill\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Human required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Human] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Divine caster required."><![CDATA[tagcount[Hero.Divine] >= 1]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fElemBlood" name="Elemental Bloodline" description="You have taken on some of the aspects of the type of element that infuses your flesh.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Base Fortitude save +4, genasi (air, earth, fire, or water).\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You gain a +4 saving throw bonus on saving throws against poison, sleep, paralysis, or stunning. You also have a 25% chance to turn a critical hit or a sneak attack against you into a normal hit (as if you were wearing light fortification armor). If you are wearing fortification armor (or a similar item or have an ability with a similar effect), use the one that has the larger percentage chance.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="+4 bonus vs poison, sleep, paralysis or stuns.  25% chance to neg crits.">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Base Fortitude +4 required."><![CDATA[child[vWill].field[vBase].value >= 4]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Genasi (Any) required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.AirGenasi] + tagis[Race.WatGenasi] + tagis[Race.FirGenasi] + tagis[Race.EarGenasi] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fEnervHeal" name="Enervative Healing" description="You can use the life energy of an opponent to heal yourself.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Fey&#146;ri, ability to use enervation as a spell-like ability.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you use your enervation ability, you may choose to touch an opponent instead of firing a ray, making a melee touch attack to do so. If the target gains negative levels, you heal 5 hit points for every negative level the target gains from this attack as if you had been healed with positive energy.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="Heal +5 hp per negative level bestowed.">
    <comment><![CDATA[Fay'ri required.
tagis[Race.Fayri] <> 0]]></comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fEyesLight" name="Eyes of Light" description="You can focus the holy power within you to create a beam of destructive light energy.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Aasimar, Celestial Bloodline.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Once per day you may fire a ray of searing light from your eyes as a spell-like ability. Your caster level for this ability is your character level. Using this ability counts as your use of light (or daylight, if you have the Light to Daylight feat) for the day.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="1/day fire ray of searing light from eyes CL = HD.">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Celestial Bloodline feat required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fCeleBlood] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Aasimar required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Aasimar] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fFienBlood" name="Fiendish Bloodline" description="Some of your latent fiendish abilities, inherited from an unusually powerful fiendish ancestor, have matured.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Fey&#146;ri, tanarukk, tiefling, base Fortitude, Reflex, and Will saves +1.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You gain the ability to cast protection from good three times per day and bane once per day as spell-like abilities with a caster level equal to your character level.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="3/day Protection from good, 1/day Bane as Spell-Like abilities. CL = char level.">
    <comment><![CDATA[Fey'ri, Tanarukk or Tiefling race required.
tagis[Race.Fayri] + tagis[Race.Tanarukk] + tagis[Race.Tiefling] <> 0

Base Saves +1 required.]]></comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Reflex save +1 required."><![CDATA[child[vRef].field[vBase].value >= 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Will save +1 required."><![CDATA[child[vWill].field[vBase].value >= 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Fortitude save +1 required."><![CDATA[child[vFort].field[vBase].value >= 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Race Fey&apos;ri, Tanarukk or Tiefling race required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Tanarukk] + tagis[Race.Tiefling] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fFGnoPhant" name="Forest Gnome Phantasist" description="You can protect your forest home with a variety of phantasms and patterns to befuddle your foes.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Forest gnome.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Your Illusion (pattern) and Illusion (phantasm) spells and spell-like abilities gain +1 spell power (+1 on save DCs and +1 bonus on checks to overcome spell resistance).\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="+1 DC and CL check to your Illusion (pattern) and (phantasm) spells.">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Forrest Gnome required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Gnome] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fGDwfDweom" name="Gold Dwarf Dweomersmith" description="You have learned the secrets of gold dwarf magic that creates or enhances weapons.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Gold dwarf.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You gain +1 caster level when casting a spell that creates a weapon or enhances an existing one.  An 11th-level caster with this feat, for example, grants a weapon a +4 enhancement bonus when she casts greater magic weapon, not just a +3 enhancement bonus.  This bonus caster level allows you to exceed the normal maximum effect allowed by a spell.\n\nThe tradition of gold dwarf dweomersmiths includes the following spells at each level:\n1st&#151;bless weapon, magic stone, magic weapon, shillelagh\n2nd&#151;flame blade, Melf&#146;s acid arrow, spiritual weapon\n3rd&#151;flame arrow, keen edge\n4th&#151;greater magic weapon, holy sword\n6th&#151;blade barrier, spellstaff\n7th&#151; changestaff, Mordenkainen&#146;s sword. Other spells gain this benefit if they target a weapon.\n\nAdditionally, any magic weapons you fashion cost 5% less in gold pieces to make.  The experience point cost is unaffected.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Gold Dwarf"><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Dwarf] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fHammFist" name="Hammer Fist" description="You are trained in an unarmed fighting style that emphasizes a two-handed strike.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Str 13, Improved Unarmed Strike, dwarf.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You add one and a half times your Strength bonus on your damage when you hit with an unarmed strike. This extra damage does not apply if you make a flurry of blows attack or if you are holding anything in either hand.  You must use both hands to make the unarmed attack.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="BonusFor" tag="Fighter"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Improved Unarmed Strike required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fImpUnarm] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Dwarf required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Dwarf] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Strength 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aSTR].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fHeadRush" name="Headlong Rush" description="You charge your foes with immense force, heedless of your own safety.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Orc or half-orc, base attack bonus +4 or higher.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Instead of a normal charge attack, you can perform a headlong rush. A headlong rush is a charge that provokes attacks of opportunity from every foe who can reach its path, including the opponent you attack. A headlong rush otherwise functions like a charge attack (+2 attack, &#150;2 AC, straight-line movement only), except that a successful attack deals double damage.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="BonusFor" tag="Fighter"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Base attack bonus +4 required."><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 4]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Orc or Half-Orc required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Orc] + tagis[Race.HalfOrc] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fHealFlame" name="Healing Flames" description="You can draw energy from open flames to heal yourself.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Base Will save +3, fire genasi or tanarukk.\n\n{b}Fire Size              Example                        Hit Points Healed{/b}\nFine                      Tindertwig                                 1\nDiminutive          Torch                                        1d3\nTiny                      Small campfire                      1d6\nSmall                   Large campfire                      2d6\nMedium-size      Forge                                        3d6\nLarge                   Bonfire                                     4d6\nHuge                    Burning shack or tree          5d6\nGargantuan        Burning tavern                       6d6\nColossal             Burning inn                              7d6\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you use your {i}control flame{/i} spell-like ability, you instead may touch the flame and heal yourself a number of hit points of damage depending upon the size of the fire. This counts as a use of your {i}control flame{/i} ability for the day.  Touching the flame causes you no harm when you use this ability, but if you enter the flame, touch more than just its edge, or remain in contact with it for more than 1 round, you take damage from the fire.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="You can draw strength from flames, healing based on fire size.">
    <comment>Added Red/Gold Dragons to the list of available choices.</comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Fire Genasi, Tanarukk or Fire-type dragons required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.FirGenasi] + tagis[Race.Tanarukk] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fHighBDrow" name="Highborn Drow" description="You have learned how to tap into the advanced magical abilities of your drow noble heritage.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Drow, base Will save +2.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You may use {i}detect good{/i}, {i}detect magic{/i}, and {i}levitate{/i} once per day as spell-like abilities with a caster level equal to your character level.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="Can use {i}detect good{/i}, {i}detect magic{/i}, and {i}levitate{/i} 1/day CL = Char  lvl.">
    <comment>Will save expr-reqs... Done</comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <usesource source="srcUndark"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="SpellLike"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Drow required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Drow] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Will save +3 required."><![CDATA[child[vWill].field[vBase].value >= 2]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fHinWander" name="Hin Wandermage" description="You have a natural affinity for spells that take you from place to place.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Lightfoot halfling.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You gain +1 caster level when casting a spell that helps you travel.  If you are a wizard, you may add a spell in your tradition to your spellbook for free when you become able to cast it. This does not count against the two free spells you add to your spellbook at each class level.\nThe tradition of the Hin wandermage consists of the following spells at the appropriate levels: \n\n0&#151;open/close\n1st&#151;expeditious retreat, mount;\n2nd&#151;endurance\n3rd&#151;fly, phantom steed, water breathing\n4th&#151;air walk, freedom of movement\n5th&#151;ethereal jaunt, plane shift, teleport\n6th&#151;find the path, transport via plants, wind walk, word of recall\n7th&#151;refuge, shadow walk, teleport without error\n8th&#151;etherealness\n9th&#151;gate, teleportation circle.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="+1 CL to any sell that helps you travel.">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Lightfoot Halfling required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Halfling] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fImpEnRes" name="Improved Energy Resistance" description="Choose one form of energy to which you have a natural (not spell- or item-granted) resistance. Your inherent resistance to this kind of energy is more effective than normal.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Naturally resistant to a form of energy (acid, cold, electricity, fire, sonic).\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Your resistance to that type of energy increases by 5. For example, if you are an aasimar, you normally have acid, cold, and electricity resistance 5. You could use this feat to increase one of those resistances to 10; the other two are unaffected.\n\n{b}Special:{/b} You can gain this feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take the feat, it applies to another type of energy to which you have a natural resistance.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <comment>Must have racial energy resist.  Granted naturally through race, template or bloodline.

Needs coding.</comment>
    <fieldval field="ftCandExpr" value="component.BaseCharge &amp; SpcReplace.xDamRs?"/>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="fSelFrom" tag="Hero"/>
    <eval phase="Final" priority="9000"><![CDATA[doneif (field[fChosen].ischosen = 0)

  var res as string

  res = "thingid." & field[fChosen].chosen.idstring

  foreach pick in hero from BaseSpec where res
   eachpick.field[Value].value += 5
  nexteach]]></eval>
    <prereq message="Natural resistance to energy required.">
      <validate><![CDATA[foreach pick in hero from BaseSpec where "SpcReplace.xDamRs?"
 validif (eachpick.tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] <> 0)
nexteach]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fImprLevit" name="Improved Levitation" description="You have learned to use part of your levitate spell-like ability at a time, allowing multiple uses with a shorter duration.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Naturally able to {i}levitate{/i} as a spell-like ability.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You may use your {i}levitate{/i} spell-like ability in 10-minute increments instead of all at once. The number of times per day you may now use the ability at this shorter duration is equal to your caster level.\n\nFor example, if you are an air genasi, you normally have the ability to {i}levitate{/i} once per day as a spell-like ability as if cast by a 5th-level sorcerer, allowing you to {i}levitate{/i} once per day for up to 50 minutes.  With this feat, you can now {i}levitate{/i} five times per day, each time for up to 10 minutes.\n\nIf you could {i}levitate{/i} more than once per day, multiply your caster level by the number of times per day to get the total number of shorter uses of {i}levitate{/i} that you have.  For example, a creature that could use {i}levitate{/i} two times per day as a spell-like ability as if cast by a 5th-level sorcerer would be able to {i}levitate{/i} 10 (2&#215;5) times per day, each time for up to 10 minutes.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="SpellLike"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fInferBarg" name="Infernal Bargainer" description="You are comfortable making deals with powerful entities from the Lower Planes.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Outsider.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Whenever you cast {i}commune, contact other plane, legend lore{/i}, or {i}vision{/i}, you gain +2 caster level because you are known to the entities answering your entreaties.\n\nWhenever you cast any {i}planar binding{/i} or {i}planar ally{/i} spell, you can call an evil creature 2 HD higher than normally allowed.\n\nAny evil creature caught in a {i}planar binding{/i} trap you create has a &#150;2 penalty on all attempts to escape.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Outsider required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.typOutside] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fIronMind" name="Iron Mind" description="You are descended from duergar who escaped enslavement by the illithids. The blood of these psionic-resistant former thralls runs thick in your veins.\n\n{i]Prerequisites:{/i} Wis 13, gray dwarf.\n\n{i}Region:{/i} Gray dwarf.\n\n{i}Benefit:{/i} You receive a +4 bonus on saving throws against psionic effects, such as those employed by a mind flayer or yuan-ti, and a +1 bonus on Will saves.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Druegar (Dwarf) required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Dwarf] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Wisdom 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aWIS].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fLighDayl" name="Light to Daylight" description="Your inherent ability to create light is more powerful than normal.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Able to use {i}light{/i} as a spell-like ability.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When using your spell-like ability to create {i}light{/i}, you may instead create {i}daylight.{/i} All other features of this ability (caster level, countering {i}darkness{/i} spells and effects) are as if you were creating {i}light{/i}. You can use your {i}light{/i} ability two additional times per day, so if you normally could use {i}light{/i} as a spell-like ability 1/day, you can now use it 3/day.\n\nFor example, if you were an aasimar, you could create either {i}light{/i} or {i}daylight{/i} three times per day as a spell-like ability, as if cast by a sorcerer of your character level.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fLightbrin" name="Lightbringer" description="You can channel positive energy into your spells so that they glow with holy power.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Damaran human, able to cast divine spells, able to turn undead.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Whenever you cast a spell, you can expend three of your daily turn attempts to infuse the spell with positive energy.\n\nEach round you do this immediately prior to casting the spell, you gain +2 spell power (+2 on save DCs and +2 bonus on checks to overcome spell resistance). Infusing a spell with positive energy is a full-round action that does not provoke attacks of opportunity. The turn attempts are wasted if you don&#146;t cast a spell immediately after spending one or more rounds infusing it.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Ability to cast divine spells required."><![CDATA[tagcount[Hero.Divine] >= 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Damaran human required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Human] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fLowBlow" name="Low Blow" description="You can get underfoot and attack creatures larger than you.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Dodge, Mobility, base attack bonus +4.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} As a full-round action, you can enter an area occupied by an opponent who is at least one size category larger than you.\n\nYou can then make a single melee attack at your highest attack bonus against this creature, who is considered flat-footed against the attack. After your attack, you return to the 5-foot square from which you entered the opponent&#146;s square. Using this feat provokes attacks of opportunity.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="BonusFor" tag="Fighter"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Mobility required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fMobility] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base attack bonus +4 required."><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 4]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Dodge required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fDodge] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fImLowBlow" name="Improved Low Blow" description="You are especially good at using the Low Blow feat.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Dodge, Mobility, Low Blow, base attack bonus +4.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Using the Low Blow feat does not provoke an attack of opportunity when you move into an opponent&#146;s square to perform the attack.\n\n{b}Normal:{/b} A character with the Low Blow feat may enter an adjacent opponent&#146;s square to make a single attack, then return to his own square. The opponent is considered flat-footed against the attack, but the character is subject to an attack of opportunity.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="BonusFor" tag="Fighter"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Mobility required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fMobility] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base attack bonus +4 required."><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 4]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Low Blow required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fLowBlow] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Dodge required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fDodge] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fMiMakeRig" name="Might Makes Right" description="Your great strength draws more followers.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Str 13, Leadership.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Add your Strength bonus to your leadership score for the purposes of determining how many followers you may have with the Leadership feat.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <exprreq message="Leadership required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fLeader] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Strength 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aSTR].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fOutsWing" name="Outsider Wings" description="You have sprouted wings appropriate to your heritage, revealing the power of your supernatural bloodline.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Aasimar or tiefling, base Fortitude, Reflex, and Will saves +2, Celestial Bloodline or Fiendish Bloodline.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You gain wings (feathered if an aasimar, batlike if a tiefling), allowing you to fly at your land speed (average maneuverability).\n\nA medium or heavy load that would reduce your land speed reduces your fly speed a proportionate amount.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <comment>Race = Aasimar or Tiefling

fFienBlood
fCeleBlood</comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xFly2"></bootstrap>
    <exprreq message="Will +2 required."><![CDATA[child[vWill].field[vBase].value >= 2]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Celestial Blood or Fiendishblood (feats) required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fCeleBlood] + #hasfeat[fFienBlood] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Fortitude +2 required."><![CDATA[child[vFort].field[vBase].value >= 2]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Reflex +2 required."><![CDATA[child[vRef].field[vBase].value >= 2]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fPlTchAnAf" name="Planetouched Animal Affinity" description="You have a special affinity for a kind of animal associated with your deity ancestor.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Aasimar, tiefling, earth genasi.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Choose a divine ancestor from the list below. You gain a +4 bonus on Animal Empathy and Handle Animal checks when dealing with animals associated with your divine ancestor.  You may make untrained Animal Empathy checks to affect such animals, as well as celestial (if you are an aasimar) or fiendish (if you are a tiefling) animals as if they were animals.\n\nSee the table for a summary of Mulhorandi deities and their favored animals.\n\n{b}Deity                      Animal{/b}\nAnhur                    Lions, horses\nBast (Sharess)    Cats, leopards, lions\nGeb                         Bears\nHathor                    Cows, bison\nHorus-Re               Hawks, lions\nIsis                          Hawks, donkeys\nNephthys               Crocodiles, hawks, poisonous snakes (primarily cobras)\nOsiris                     Bears, hawks\nSebek                    Crocodiles\nSet                          Poisonous snakes\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="+4 Animal Empathy and Handle Animal on selected animal.">
    <comment>Create dropdown menu

Race Aasimar + Tiefling + EarGenasi</comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fPrimCastr" name="Primitive Caster" description="You use screeches, wild gesticulations, and extra material components to give your spells additional power.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} This feat only functions when you cast a spell that does not already have a verbal, somatic, or material component.\n\nFor each component you voluntarily add, you increase the effective level of the spell by +1. You can only add a component that&#146;s not already present in the spell. For example, you can&#146;t add a somatic component to a gaseous form spell, because it already has one. You could add a verbal component, however.\n\nThe verbal component you add consists of animalistic shouts, screams, and growls. The DC of Listen checks to hear you cast a spell is &#150;5 (before modifying for distance). The somatic component is also more complex, so you must have two hands free to add a somatic component with this feat. The extra material component you add with this feat must be a rare plant found in the forest with a successful Profession (herbalist) check (DC 15).\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRapSwim" name="Rapid Swimming" description="You are one with the water.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Base Fortitude save +2, natural swim speed.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Your swim speed increases by 20 feet.\n\n{b}Normal:{/b} A water genasi normally has a swim speed of 30 feet.\nAn aquatic elf normally has a swim speed of 40 feet.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="+20 to swim speed.">
    <comment>must have a natural swim speed.</comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Base Fortitude +2 required."><![CDATA[child[vWill].field[vBase].value >= 2]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fReckOffen" name="Reckless Offensive" description="You lower your guard in order to make a telling attack.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Base attack bonus +2, Power Attack.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} On your action, before making attack rolls for a round, you may choose to take a &#150;4 penalty to your AC during the round to gain a +2 competence bonus on all melee attacks in the same round. The penalty to AC and bonus on melee attacks apply until your next action. You cannot use Reckless Offensive with ranged attacks.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="+2 comp bon to all attacks; -4 AC for one round.">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="BonusFor" tag="Fighter"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Power Attack required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fPowerAtt] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base attack +2 required."><![CDATA[child[vWill].field[vBase].value >= 2]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRckGnTric" name="Rock Gnome Trickster" description="Your glamers are particularly likely to fool the senses of your target.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Rock gnome.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Your Illusion (glamer) spells and spell-like abilities gain +1 spell power (+1 on save DCs and +1 bonus on checks to overcome spell resistance).\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="+1 to your Illusion(Glamer) DC&apos;s and CL checks.">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRunesmith" name="Runesmith" description="You can fashion runes that take the place of material components for your spells.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} 4 ranks in Craft (rune).\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You can make runes that take the place of traditional material components for spells you cast. The runes, often carved into stone talismans or stamped onto small plates of metal, cost 1 gp each and have a Craft (rune) DC of 15. Unlike a material component, a rune does not disappear when you cast a spell; having this feat effectively turns a material component required for a spell into a focus.\n\nYour use of runes makes your spells more difficult to counterspell.\nOther spellcasters who observe you casting a spell take a &#150;4 penalty on checks to determine which spell you&#146;re casting, unless they also have the Runesmith feat.\n\nSpells with costly material components are unaffected by this feat.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="Crafts material components into runes. (making permenent spell foc).">
    <comment>Add Craft (Rune)</comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSacTattoo" name="Sacred Tattoo" description="You have been spiritually touched by one of the god-kings of the Old Empires and bear his or her symbol in the form of a tattoo in the shape of a holy symbol.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Patron deity from the Mulhorandi or Untheric pantheon.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Add +1 to the DC for all saving throws against spells you cast in an area consecrated/desecrated or hallowed/unhallowed to your deity. You get a +1 bonus on caster level checks to beat a creature&#146;s spell resistance when casting spells in such areas.\n\n{b}Special:{/b} It is not possible to take both this feat and the Tattoo Magic feat.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="+1 DC and CL checks to all spells cast on ground sacred to your deity.">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Thayan Tattoos forbidden.">#hasfeat[fTatFoc] = 0</exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fShDwaWard" name="Shield Dwarf Warder" description="You are a student of the protective magics of the shield dwarves, learned at great cost during centuries of warfare and wandering.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Shield dwarf.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You gain +1 caster level when casting a spell that creates or enhances a suit of armor or a shield.\n\nThe tradition of shield dwarf warders includes the following spells at the appropriate levels:\n\n1st&#151;entropic shield, mage armor, shield, shield of faith\n2nd&#151;shield other\n3rd&#151;magic vestment\n4th&#151;fire shield\n6th&#151;stone body\n8th&#151;iron body, shield of law.\n\nOther spells gain this benefit if they target a suit of armor or shield.\nAdditionally, any magic armor or shield you create costs 5% less gold pieces to make. The experience point cost is unaffected.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Shield Dwarf required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Dwarf] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSoMagicia" name="Southern Magician" description="Your magical studies in Mulan lands have taught you spellcasting techniques unknown in the north that blur the line between arcane and divine magic.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Mulan human, ability to cast 2nd-level spells.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Once per day per two spellcaster levels, you can cast a divine spell as an arcane spell, or vice versa. This enables you to bypass arcane spell failure due to armor, or gain additional benefit from spell that functions differently for a divine caster instead of an arcane caster, such as true seeing or magic weapon.\n\nSpells changed with this feat are often confusing to whose who haven&#146;t studied Mulan magic. Spellcasters who don&#146;t have this feat suffer a &#150;4 penalty on attempts to counterspell or dispel this spell, and they must succeed at a caster level check (DC 11 + spell level) to detect the spell with detect magic.\n\nThe actual source of the spell&#146;s power doesn&#146;t change, nor does its means of preparation. You are merely weaving the strands of magic together in an unconventional way that makes the spell behave somewhat differently.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="The line between arcane and divine blurs for your spells.">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <exprreq message="Must be able to cast 2nd level spells."><![CDATA[tagcount[Hero.Divine] + tagcount[Hero.Arcane] >= 2 + 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Mulani Human required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Human] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSpAbFoc" name="Spell-Like Ability Focus" description="Choose one of your spell-like abilities. This attack becomes more potent than normal.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Spell-like ability.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Add +2 to the DC for all saving throws against the spell-like ability on which you focus.\n\n{b}Special:{/b} You can gain this feat multiple times.  Its effects do not stack. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a new spelllike ability.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="You gain a +2 bonus to the DC of a special attack.">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General" name="General" abbrev="General"/>
    <tag group="fShowWhat" tag="Freeform" name="Freeform edit control" abbrev="Freeform edit control"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fStagStrik" name="Staggering Strike" description="You are particularly adept at making cruel and demoralizing sneak attacks.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Base attack bonus +6, sneak attack ability.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} If you hit with a sneak attack, you may choose to forgo a variable number (chosen by you at the time of the strike) of dice of sneak attack damage to deliver a particularly horrifying and disgusting wound. The victim of a staggering strike becomes staggered for a number of rounds equal to one-third the number of dice of damage you choose to forgo. For example, if you could sneak attack for +6d6 damage, you could forgo all that extra damage to stagger the target for 2 rounds.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat">
    <comment>requires sneak attack, or sudden strike</comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="BonusFor" tag="Fighter"/>
    <exprreq message="Base attack bonus +6 required."><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 6]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fStonebloo" name="Stoneblood" description="Your blood is thick like cooling lava, making it difficult for you to die after falling from injuries.\n\n{bPrerequisites:{/b} Con 13, urdunnir.\n\n{b}Region:{/b} Urdunnir.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When dying, you have a 50% chance per round to stabilize and stop bleeding to death.\n\n{b}Normal:{/b} A character normally has a 10% chance to stabilize when dying.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="Have a 50% chance of stabilzing to stop bleeding to death.">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Constitution 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aCON].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Urdunnir (Dwarf) required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Dwarf] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fStonColos" name="Stone Colossus" description="You can focus a part of your power to increase the toughness of your skin.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Base Fortitude save +3, earth genasi.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you use the attack action or full attack action in melee, you can take a penalty of as much as &#150;5 on your attack and add the same number (up to +5) to your Armor Class as a natural armor bonus. This number may not exceed your base attack bonus. The changes to attack rolls and Armor Class last until your next action.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="Focus power sacrificing Attack for Armor (max 5).">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="BonusFor" tag="Fighter"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Earth Genasi required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.EarGenasi] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base fortitude save +3 required."><![CDATA[child[vFort].field[vBase].value >= 3]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fStoneWFis" name="Stonewalker Fist" description="You are trained in an unarmed fighting style that draws on your ability to pass through minerals as if they were air.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Improved Unarmed Strike, urdunnir.\n\n{b}Region:{/b} Urdunnir.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} By altering the elemental structure of your fists in order to strike through a creature&#146;s armor, you may ignore up to a +4 armor bonus due to metal or stone armor or shields. (This in no way affects or damages the armor.) You cannot use this ability on creatures with the earth subtype. Using this ability is a free action.\n\n{b}Special:{/b} A character may gain this feat twice at most, but the effects stack." compset="Feat" maxlimit="2">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="BonusFor" tag="Fighter"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Urdunnir (Dwarf) required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Dwarf] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Improved Unarmed Strike required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fImpUnarm] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSumEaElem" name="Summon Earth Elemental" description="Like many experienced deep gnomes, you have developed the ability to summon earth elementals to help you with tasks.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Deep gnome, character level 6th.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Once per day, you may summon an earth elemental. If acting alone, you may only summon a Small earth elemental. For each additional deep gnome employing this feat in conjunction with you, you may summon an earth elemental one size larger (see the table on Monster Manual page 83). For example, a group of four deep gnomes with this feat can summon a Huge earth elemental, and a group of six deep gnomes can summon an elder earth elemental. Working together in this fashion uses this ability for all involved gnomes for the day.\n\nThis is a spell-like ability and is treated as if the characters involved are casting a summon monster spell of the appropriate level, with the exception that they can only summon earth elementals.\n\nUnlike the spell, you cannot use this ability to summon multiple elementals at a time.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="Can summ earth element, Small alone, +2 helpers for each size larger.">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Must be of 6th level."><![CDATA[#totallevelcount[] >= 6]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Deep Gnome required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Gnome] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSvirfFigm" name="Svirfneblin Figment Master" description="Your time underground has made you acutely aware of even slight differences in sound and vision in caves that have never seen the sun. Accordingly, your illusions are finely tuned and ultra-realistic.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Deep gnome.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Your Illusion (figment) spells and spell-like abilities gain +1 spell power (+1 on save DCs and +1 bonus on checks to overcome spell resistance).\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="+1 to DC&apos;s and CL checks to your Illusion (figments)">
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <exprreq message="Deep Gnome required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Gnome] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSwarmfig" name="Swarmfighting" description="You and allies with this feat can coordinate melee attacks against a single target and are adept at fighting side by side in close quarters.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Small size, Dex 13, base attack bonus +1.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You can occupy the same 5-foot square in combat with any other allied Small creature that also possesses the Swarmfighting feat at no penalty. When you engage a Medium or larger creature in melee, and at least one other ally with the Swarmfighting feat threatens the target, you gain a +1 morale bonus on the attack roll. This bonus increases by +1 for each additional ally beyond the first with the Swarmfighting feat that threatens the same target. The total morale bonus imparted to your attack roll cannot exceed your Dexterity bonus.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="No pen in same sq as ally with feat, +1 to att for each threatening Med+ foe." replaces="fSwarmfigh" uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre req (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="CompWarrio" parent="p35" name="Complete Warrior"/>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <tag group="BonusFor" tag="Fighter"/>
    <exprreq message="Small size required.">herofield[tSize].value = -1</exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base attack bonus +1 required."><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Dexterity 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aDEX].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fTalfSong" name="Talfirian Song" description="You can use the power of your bardic music to enhance your Illusion spells.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Bardic music class feature, Heighten Spell, Tethyrian human.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} By expending uses of your bardic music, you can heighten your illusion spells without using higher-level spell slots. For every daily use of your bardic music you expend during the casting of a spell, you can increase the effective level of that spell by +1. For example, you could cast {i}rainbow pattern{/i} and expend four uses of your bardic music to make that {i}rainbow pattern{/i} effectively an 8th-level spell (increasing the save DC by +4).\n\nYou can&#146;t raise a spell above 9th level with this feat.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="Expend Bardic Music to highten illusion spells without using higher slot.">
    <comment>add requirement for Bardic Music requirement.</comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <exprreq message="Talfirian Human required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Human] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Heighten Spell required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fHeightSpl] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fTattooMag" name="Tattoo Magic" description="You can create tattoos that store spells.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Craft (calligraphy) or Craft (painting) skill, spellcaster level 3rd.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You can create single-use magic tattoos. You can create a tattoo of any spell of 3rd level or lower that you know and that targets a creature or creatures. Creating a tattoo takes 1 hour, and it must be inked onto a creature with a corporeal body. When you create a tattoo, you set the caster level. The caster level must be sufficient to cast the spell in question and no higher than your own level. The base price of a tattoo is its spell level &#215; its caster level &#215; 50 gp. To create a tattoo, you must spend 1/25th of this base price in XP and use up raw materials costing half this base price.\n\nWhen you create a tattoo, you make any choices that you would normally make when casting the spell. The bearer of the tattoo is the only one who can activate it and is always the target of the spell. Activating a tattoo requires the creature to touch the tattoo with either hand (the hand does not need to be empty). Activating a tattoo is a standard action that does not draw an attack of opportunity.\n\nAny tattoo that stores a spell with a costly material component or an XP cost also carries a commensurate cost. In addition to the costs derived from the base price, you must expend the material component or pay the XP when creating the tattoo.\n\nNormally, a magic tattoo uses a magic item space on the creature&#146;s body. For example, a creature with a tattoo on one of its hands could not gain the benefit from a magic glove on that hand. Likewise, a creature with a magic tattoo on its back does not receive the benefits of a magic cloak, cape, or mantle. In effect, the magic tattoo is always the first item &#147;worn&#148; on that part of the body, negating the effects of all other items. A tattoo can be created that does not use a magic item space, but the base price of such a tattoo is double the normal value.\n\nA magic tattoo can be erased with an erase spell as if it were magic writing. Failing to erase the tattoo does not activate it.\n\nWhen a tattoo is activated, the ink pattern or design vanishes from the bearer&#146;s skin.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="Can imbue single-use spells onto a body with a Tattoo.">
    <comment>Craft (Calligraphy or Craft (Painting) doesnt exsist.</comment>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="ItemCreate"/>
    <exprreq message="Caster level 3 required."><![CDATA[herofield[tMaxCaster].value >= 3]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fWatAdapt2" name="Water Adaptation" description="You favor your aquatic elf parent and have developed the ability to breathe and move about in water easily.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Aquatic half-elf.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You can breathe water as well as air. Your swim speed improves to 20 feet.\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: Aquatic half-elves without this feat cannot breathe water and have a swim speed of 15 feet.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Races of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="You can breath water as well as air, swim speed increases to 20 ft." replaces="fWatAdapt" uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre req (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="SrcStormWr" parent="p35" name="Stormwrack"/>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Racial"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostAt">hero.childfound[xSwim].field[Value].value += 5</eval>
    <exprreq message="Aquatic half-elf race required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.ElfAquatic] + tagis[Race.HalfElf] >= 2]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="wAsperHeav" name="Aspergillum, Heavy" description="The common aspergillum (detailed in the {i}FORGOTTEN REALMS Campaign Setting{/i}, page 95) is a lightweight metal device resembling a small club or light mace with a perforated head for dispensing holy water.\nAlthough not a weapon per se, it can be used in combat to deliver ranged touch attacks.\nThe heavy aspergillum combines the properties of a common aspergillum with those of a heavy mace and is greatly favored by members of the Impilturan church of Ilmater. A heavy aspergillum can hold up to 3 flasks of holy water. In addition to serving as a common aspergillum, it can also be used in melee combat. When a button on the shaft is pressed, tiny holes open in the mace head, allowing holy water to touch a creature struck by the weapon. Each use of the weapon in this manner uses one flask of holy water per attack whether or not the attack is successful. If the wielder has multiple attacks per round with the weapon, the holy water can be released multiple times in one round (but no more than once per attack) until it is depleted. A heavy aspergillum may also be used to make ranged touch attacks with holy water in the manner of a normal aspergillum.\nPouring a flask of holy water into an aspergillum or heavy aspergillum is a standard action that provokes an attack of opportunity." compset="Weapon">
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="12"/>
    <fieldval field="gSizeCost" value="100"/>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="wCritMin" tag="20"/>
    <tag group="wCritMult" tag="2"/>
    <tag group="EquipType" tag="Metal"/>
    <tag group="wMain" tag="1d8_6"/>
    <tag group="wCategory" tag="Melee"/>
    <tag group="wType" tag="B"/>
