  <thing id="gArmorLubr" name="Armor Lubricant" description="This nonmagical oil reduces the friction that impedes movement in metallic armor.  One application of armor lubricant reduces the armor check penalty by 1 (to a minimum of 0).  Each application takes 1 minute to apply and lasts 1d4 hours.  It is not possible to apply armor lubricant to armor currently being worn. Armor lubricant provides no benefit to shields or to armor not made primarily of metal.\nCreating one application of armor lubricant requires a successful Alchemy check (DC 15) and follows the rules outlined in the discussion of Craft skills in the {i}Player&#146;s Handbook{/i}." compset="Gear" summary="Reduces armor check penalty by 1 for 1d4 hours.">
