  <thing id="ioFigDolph" name="Figurine, Coral Dolphin" description="Coral Dolphin: Made by a water genasi mage, this finely carved dolphin of white coral can transform into a living dolphin, except that it possesses an Intelligence of 8 and the ability to \nspeak and understand Common and Aquan. The dolphin is treated as a magical beast when in its living form. It may be used twice per tenday for up to 4 hours each use.\nCaster Level: 11th; Prerequisites: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}animate objects{/i}, {i}water breathing{/i}; Market Price: 10,000 gp; Weight: &#151;." compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="10000"/>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder" name="Wondrous Item" abbrev="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioFigBEagl" name="Figurine, Blue Quartz Eagle" description="Blue Quartz Eagle: A blue quartz eagle becomes an eagle on command, but with vision akin to that granted by eyes of the eagle (+5 circumstance bonus on Spot checks).\nAnother command sends it aloft. It will not attack, even to defend itself, but it will obey the telepathic commands of its owner as long as it remains within one mile of her. If forced to \nmove beyond that distance, a blue quartz eagle will immediately revert to statuette form (usually shattering if it falls a great distance to the ground). While the figurine is transformed, its owner can mentally view everything the eagle can see, although the owner must use a standard action to observe what the eagle sees in that round. It can maintain its nonfigurine status for only 24 hours per tenday, but the duration need not be continuous.\n\nCaster Level: 11th; Prerequisites: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}animate objects{/i}, {i}clairaudience/clairvoyance{/i}; Market Price: 5,400 gp; Weight: &#151;." compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="10000"/>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder" name="Wondrous Item" abbrev="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipGogondy" name="Bottle of Gogondy" description="This ruby wine, fermented by the deep gnomes, gives visions to those who drink it. Anyone who consumes a glass of Gogondy should roll on the following table:\n\n{b}d%            Result                                                                                        Side effect{/b}\n01&#150;15     Nothing happens                                                                    1d3 temporary Dex, 1d3 temporary Int\n16&#150;30     Divination spell (10th-level caster)                                    1d6 temporary Dex, 1d3 temporary Int\n31&#150;60     Vision spell on tangential topic                                          1d6 temporary Dex, 1d6 temporary Int\n61&#150;80     Contact other plane (elemental plane of earth;                                      NONE\n                                                      10th-level caster) as spell\n81&#150;90     Vision spell on topic you specify                                       2d6 temporary Dex, 2d6 temporary Int\n91&#150;00     Contact other plane (outer plane/intermediate;                                      NONE\n                                                      10th-level caster) as spell\n\nA full bottle of Gogondy holds enough wine for six glasses.\nCaster Level: 14th; Prerequisites: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}divination{/i}, {i}contact other plane{/i}, creator must be a deep gnome; Market Price: 3,000 gp; Weight: 5 lb." compset="OilPotion">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="3000"/>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="OilPotion"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioHamWeap" name="Hammer of the Weaponsmith" description="Hammer of the Weaponsmith: This masterwork tool gives the user a +10 circumstance bonus on Craft (weaponsmithing) checks.\nCaster Level: 6th; Prerequisites: Craft Wondrous Item, creator must be at least 6th level; Market Price: 2,055 gp; Cost to Create: 1,055 gp + 80 XP; Weight: 8 lb." compset="Wondrous">
